      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's a fundamental principle of democracy that everyone is subject to the same laws, ensuring equal protection under the law and preventing the erosion of democratic values. Allowing religious groups to opt out of certain mandates based on their faith can create a slippery slope where certain groups are granted special treatment, undermining the very fabric of democracy. In fact, the US Supreme Court has consistently ruled that the government cannot accommodate the religious objections of individuals or organizations in a way that discriminates against others. This approach promotes a more inclusive and equitable society where all citizens are treated with dignity and respect.",
