      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Exemptions are not inherently problematic, but the issue lies in the context and the motivations behind them. Disability accommodations and medical needs are not inherently subjective or value-based, whereas religious beliefs are often deeply personal and subjective. Allowing exemptions for religious groups can create a slippery slope where certain groups are granted special treatment based on their values, which can be at odds with the values of the majority.",
